CASE
  WHEN condition_1 THEN result_1
  WHEN condition_2 THEN result_2
END
Case statement evaluates a list of conditions and returns a value when the first condition is met

Use Cases:
1. Derive new information - create a new columns based on existing data. Example - categorizung data - group
data into categories based on certain conditions (categorize sales on high, medium. low)
2. Mapping - transform data from on form to another (ex, country name --> country code (Germany --> DE)
3. Handling NULLs - replace NULL with a specific value
4. Conditional Aggregation - apply aggregate functions only to subset of data that fulfill certain conditions 
(example, for each customer, count number of orders greater than 30) 
